h a nice transparent fake sim on it  saying: "Don''t use before activating 4G" or something similar, I don''t  remember and already dumped the card) which is OVERLY confusing! What is  that supposed to mean? The 3G network is working fine in Marin  County... I guess I''ll have to go SF Downtown to get 4G... but it is  working with no SIM card on it! So... how come is this the unlocked  version? What is that SIM card slot used for? Will it work with my Costa  Rican SIM? I''ll have to wait to go back to CR to verify... so far look  scary and confusing.\r\n\r\nBut maybe the most frustrating part is the hundreds of dollars of Apps I  have on my iPad are there on the  Android Marketplace... same App, same  developers, same sellers, same price.... but I''m supposed to buy them  again to get them on Android... don''t expect a major migration from iPad  to Android if people can at least get a radical discount for apps they  already own in a different platform!\r\n\r\nSo... all in all at least I have Flash right? WRONG! Adobe''s Flash  player welcomes my Honeycomb experience with a shiny: There is no Flash  Player for your current OS Version (Honeycomb 3.0).\r\n\r\nI feel like Britney Spears drunk getting married in Vegas! My Honeymoon  with Honeycomb was not that good as my first night with the iPad... but  well I guess true love means aging together while maturing and getting  to know each other on time.... Android seems like the promise of true  love, and makes the iPad look like a spoiled gorgeous primma donna which  had me hypnotized with her enchants for the last year.\r\n\r\nTime to grow up!', 'My Honeymoon with Honeycomb', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'my-honeymoon-with-honeycomb', '', '', '2011-05-17 00:34:19', '2011-05-17 06:34:19', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8080/geeksomnio/?p=54', 0, 'post', '', 0),
