r portraited  above is trying to reach....\r\n<h2>As a regular user (Not a hardcore  geek)</h2>\r\nCustomization is cool... but not to the point where your  options include 16745 applications to change backgrounds, 6743 to track  your memory usage (you`d be surprised to know that the majority of the  people don`t even realize their phones have a memory). 887745 apps to  hack the kernel, and even some old school folks in WM tweaking the  registry! While the app you`re looking for is buried pages and pages  underneath those customizatrion demons.\r\n\r\nI know that the geek in you  is screaming THIS GUY IS SOO WRONG! Well... if you enjoy tweaking your  hardware to get 300fps on a game even knowing that 300fps is not  noticable by human eyes... because THAT is the fun part of the game....  more than the game itself... then think twice! Customization is your  thing... but you`re a small portion of the mass market....\r\n\r\nSo...  am I an iOS fanboy? Not at all... I had big hopes on the Nexus phone as a  google plattform distributed, manufactered and kept under certain  standards... But tose standards went to zero in a heartbeat by releasing  the OS... If things continue so in the wild... the next iPhone killer  will certainly come out of Coupertino....', 'your shiny new android', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '58-revision-2', '', '', '2011-05-17 01:22:45', '2011-05-17 07:22:45', '', 58, 'http://localhost:8080/geeksomnio/2011/05/17/58-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
